<body>
  <head>XPath Cheat Sheet</head>
  <test>//</test>
  <div>
    <head>Shortcuts</head>
    <ul>
      <li>//</li>
      <li>*</li>
      <li>node()</li>
      <li>.</li>
      <li>..</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <head>Types of Results</head>
    <ul>
      <li>Node-set</li>
      <li>Boolean</li>
      <li>Number</li>
      <li>String</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <head>Types of Nodes</head>
    <ul>
      <li>element</li>
      <li>attribute</li>
      <li>comment</li>
      <li>namespace</li>
      <li>text</li>
      <li>processing instruction</li>
      <li>document</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <head>Axis Relations</head>
    <ul>
      <ul>
        <lh>Reverse axes (before "self")</lh>
        <li>ancestor</li>
        <li>ancestor-or-self</li>
        <li>parent</li>
        <li>preceding</li>
        <li>preceding-sibling</li>
      </ul>
      <li>self</li>
      <ul>
        <lh>Forward axes (after "self")</lh>
        <li>following-sibling</li>
        <li>following</li>
        <li>child</li>
        <li>descendant-or-self</li>
        <li>descendant</li>
      </ul>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      <li>namespace</li>
      <li>attribute</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <head>Functions</head>
    <p>XPath functions are also used in XQuery and XSLT! See the <ref target="http://www.w3schools.com/xpath/xpath_functions.asp">awesome and comprehensive list of functions</ref> at W3Schools for functions which didn't make it onto this list.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>not()</li>
      <li>name()</li>
      <li>local-name()</li>
      <li>empty()</li>
      <li>exists()</li>
      <li>count()</li>
      <li>distinct-values()</li>
      <li>position()</li>
      <ul>
        <lh>Strings</lh>
        <li>string()</li>
        <li>concat()</li>
        <li>string-join()</li>
        <li>normalize-space()</li>
        <li>contains()</li>
        <li>starts-with()</li>
        <li>ends-with()</li>
        <li>matches()</li>
        <li>replace()</li>
        <li>tokenize()</li>
      </ul>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
